    <rigor-reason>Modifies both BFF (.cs DTO + persistence service) and frontend (.tsx + .ts) code. Touches the Cosmos schema (additive). Multi-file dependency graph. Code-review + adr-check required at Step 9.5.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>none</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Touches WorkspaceTabManager.ts and WorkspacePane.tsx (both modified by earlier Phase C tasks); touches BFF persistence DTO. Sequential remediation only.</parallel-reason>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Close the NFR-09 gap surfaced by task 063: non-Home workspace tabs are not persisted across page refresh. Extend the existing R2 SessionPersistenceService schema with a tabs[] field, wire write-through on tab mutations from WorkspaceTabManager, and restore tabs on WorkspacePane mount. This is the strict-compliance path for the spec's NFR-09 acceptance criterion: "open 3 non-Home tabs + refresh → all 3 tabs (and active selection) restored."
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Full-stack engineer with .NET 8 Minimal API + Cosmos DB persistence experience AND React 19 + TypeScript familiarity. Comfortable making coordinated frontend + backend changes that preserve backwards compatibility.
  </role>

  <goal>
    A working tab persistence pipeline: (a) `StoredSession.Tabs: List&lt;StoredWorkspaceTab&gt;` field added in BFF; (b) `SessionPersistenceService` writes tabs through on every mutation; (c) `WorkspaceTabManager.serializeForPersistence()` + `restoreFromPersistence(tabs)` methods added; (d) `WorkspacePane.tsx` wires write-through after addTab/closeTab/setActiveTab/clearAllTabs and calls restore on mount; (e) NFR-09 acceptance test passes manually OR via an automated test.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Task 063 backwards-compat verification confirmed UQ-03: `WorkspaceTabManager.ts` has no persistence (no localStorage, no sessionStorage, no BFF write-through). R2's `SessionPersistenceService` serializes AI session state (messages, widgetStates, summary) to Cosmos but NOT the workspace tabs array. So when the user opens 3 non-Home tabs and refreshes the page, all 3 are lost.

      NFR-09 explicitly requires: "Tabs (Home + non-Home) and active workspace layout survive page refresh via existing session-restore pipeline (Cosmos write-through, R2 D-06)."

      The fix extends the existing pipeline rather than introducing a new persistence layer. R2 D-06 (write-through Cosmos persistence) is the canonical pattern — we just add the tabs payload to the existing flow.

      **Key files**:
      - Server-side schema: [`src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Sessions/StoredSession.cs`](../../src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Sessions/StoredSession.cs) — Cosmos DTO; partition key `/tenantId`; already has `WidgetStates: Dictionary&lt;string, string&gt;` and `Messages: List&lt;SessionMessage&gt;` patterns to follow
      - Server-side persistence: [`src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Sessions/SessionPersistenceService.cs`](../../src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Sessions/SessionPersistenceService.cs) — implements ISessionPersistenceService; has Save/Load methods
      - Server-side interface: [`src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Sessions/ISessionPersistenceService.cs`](../../src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Sessions/ISessionPersistenceService.cs)
      - Server-side restore: [`src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Sessions/SessionRestoreService.cs`](../../src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Sessions/SessionRestoreService.cs)
      - Client-side tab manager: [`src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/workspace/WorkspaceTabManager.ts`](../../src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/workspace/WorkspaceTabManager.ts) — plain TypeScript class; `WorkspaceTab` interface has `Component: React.ComponentType` (not serializable — must exclude)
      - Client-side WorkspacePane: [`src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/workspace/WorkspacePane.tsx`](../../src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/workspace/WorkspacePane.tsx) — owns the tab manager and the BFF call sites; uses `authenticatedFetch` from `@spaarke/auth`
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Sessions/StoredSession.cs</file>
