      <file>tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/Sessions/SessionPersistenceServiceTests.cs (if exists; else colocate new)</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="spec">NFR-09 (Persistence): Tabs (Home + non-Home) and active workspace layout survive page refresh via existing session-restore pipeline.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec">FR-25 / NFR-10: Standalone LegalWorkspace MUST continue to function identically. The tab-persistence change is SpaarkeAi-only — LegalWorkspace must not be affected.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">AI architecture: extend the BFF in-process; no new service.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-015">Cosmos sessions container partition key is `/tenantId`. Tabs[] field is additive to existing StoredSession DTO.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-028">All client→BFF calls use `authenticatedFetch` from `@spaarke/auth`. No token snapshots.</constraint>
    <constraint source="root-CLAUDE.md §10">BFF Hygiene — extension stays within `Sprk.Bff.Api`, no new DI module. Cite placement decision in code comment.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-010">No new DI feature modules; register any new service in an existing module.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Component instances (React.ComponentType) are NOT serializable. `serializeForPersistence()` must extract only `{id, kind, widgetType, widgetData, displayName}` — the Component is re-resolved via `resolveWorkspaceWidget(widgetType)` on restore.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Home tab is canonical and not persisted (it's recreated by `ensureHomeTab()` on every mount). Only non-Home tabs need to be serialized.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Write-through must be debounced/coalesced — rapid tab operations (e.g., FIFO eviction adding+removing) should not flood the BFF with parallel saves. Use a small queue or last-write-wins with ~200ms debounce.</constraint>
  </constraints>

