  <steps>
    <step order="1" name="Investigate existing persistence pipeline">
      Read SessionPersistenceService.cs and ISessionPersistenceService.cs to understand the current Save/Load API. Find the existing call sites (where ChatSessionManager / ChatEndpoints invokes Save). Confirm the write-through pattern. Verify the StoredSession DTO field-add is additive and backwards-compatible (Cosmos document evolves cleanly — older docs without Tabs field will deserialize with `Tabs == null` or empty list).
    </step>
    <step order="2" name="Define StoredWorkspaceTab record">
      In `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Sessions/`, add `StoredWorkspaceTab.cs` (record or class with `[JsonPropertyName]` attributes):
      ```csharp
      public record StoredWorkspaceTab(
          [property: JsonPropertyName("id")] string Id,
          [property: JsonPropertyName("widgetType")] string WidgetType,
          [property: JsonPropertyName("widgetData")] JsonElement? WidgetData,
          [property: JsonPropertyName("displayName")] string DisplayName);
      ```
      Note: `kind` is omitted because Home is not persisted (always recreated by ensureHomeTab). Only widget kind reaches this DTO.
      `widgetData` uses `JsonElement` for opaque pass-through — server doesn't interpret payload, just stores it for re-hydration on restore.
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Extend StoredSession schema">
      Edit `StoredSession.cs` — add field after `WidgetStates`:
      ```csharp
      /// &lt;summary&gt;
      /// Workspace tabs (non-Home only) persisted via write-through (NFR-09).
      /// Home tab is recreated by ensureHomeTab() on every WorkspacePane mount and
      /// is not persisted. Tab order is preserved. Empty list for sessions that
      /// have no non-Home tabs open.
      /// &lt;/summary&gt;
      [JsonPropertyName("tabs")]
      public List&lt;StoredWorkspaceTab&gt; Tabs { get; set; } = [];

      /// &lt;summary&gt;
      /// Active tab id at the time of the last save. May be the Home tab id ("home")
      /// or one of the ids in Tabs. Used by the client on restore to set the
      /// active selection.
      /// &lt;/summary&gt;
      [JsonPropertyName("activeTabId")]
      public string? ActiveTabId { get; set; }
      ```
      Both fields default-initialised so older Cosmos docs deserialise cleanly.
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Extend ISessionPersistenceService + SessionPersistenceService">
      Find the existing Save/Update method signatures in ISessionPersistenceService.cs and SessionPersistenceService.cs. Add (or modify) a method `SaveTabsAsync(sessionId, tenantId, tabs, activeTabId, ct)` that:
      - Loads existing StoredSession by (sessionId, tenantId)
      - Updates only the Tabs + ActiveTabId fields (and LastActivity)
      - Saves back via the existing Cosmos UpsertAsync pattern
      - Optimistic concurrency / no-op if session not found (return false; client should handle gracefully)
      Alternatively: extend existing Save method to accept tabs as an optional parameter — choose whichever matches existing patterns better.
      DI registration: per ADR-010, register in the EXISTING AiPersistenceModule.cs (no new module). Verify registration is unchanged unless adding a new public method requires a new interface method.
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Add HTTP endpoint for tab write-through">
      In an appropriate endpoint file (most likely the same AI endpoints group — e.g., `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/Ai/ChatEndpoints.cs` if sessions live there, OR a sibling like `SessionEndpoints.cs`), add a new MapPost route:
      ```
      PATCH /api/ai/chat/sessions/{sessionId}/tabs
      Body: { tabs: [...], activeTabId?: string }
      ```
      MUST inherit existing endpoint filter chain: `.AddAiAuthorizationFilter().RequireRateLimiting("ai-stream")` (or equivalent — preserve ADR-008 compliance). Return 204 NoContent on success; 404 if session doesn't exist.
      Test the endpoint compiles and `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/` is clean.
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Extend WorkspaceTabManager with serialize/restore">
      Add methods to `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/workspace/WorkspaceTabManager.ts`:
      ```ts
      /** Serializable view of a non-Home tab. */
      export interface SerializableWorkspaceTab {
        id: string;
        widgetType: string;
        widgetData: unknown;
        displayName: string;
      }

      /** Returns serializable snapshot of non-Home tabs only (Home is recreated by ensureHomeTab). */
      serializeForPersistence(): { tabs: SerializableWorkspaceTab[]; activeTabId: string | null }

      /** Replaces non-Home tabs from a persisted snapshot. Resolves widget components asynchronously. Idempotent. */
      restoreFromPersistence(snapshot: { tabs: SerializableWorkspaceTab[]; activeTabId: string | null }): Promise&lt;void&gt;
      ```
      Restore semantics:
      - Skip restore if there's already a non-Home tab open (avoid clobbering current session state).
      - Resolve each `widgetType` via the existing `resolveWorkspaceWidget(widgetType)` factory — re-hydrates the Component.
      - Set active tab to `snapshot.activeTabId` if it's in the restored set, else keep current.
      - Emit no events; mutations call existing onChange callback so React state updates naturally.
    </step>
    <step order="7" name="Wire write-through in WorkspaceTabManager mutation methods">
      Modify the WorkspaceTabManager class to call a new `onPersistChange?: (snapshot) => void` callback after every state-mutating operation (`addTab`, `closeTab`, `setActiveTab`, `clearAllTabs`). The callback is injected by `WorkspacePane.tsx`. Debounce the callback at the WorkspacePane level (not in the manager) to avoid coupling React to the plain TS class.
    </step>
    <step order="8" name="Wire write-through + restore in WorkspacePane.tsx">
      Modify `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/workspace/WorkspacePane.tsx`:

      **Write-through (on every state change)**:
      Add a debounced (200ms) effect that POSTs to `PATCH /api/ai/chat/sessions/{sessionId}/tabs` via `authenticatedFetch` whenever the manager emits onPersistChange. Use `useDebouncedEffect` or a simple `useEffect` + `setTimeout` + cleanup. Body = `manager.serializeForPersistence()`.

      **Restore on mount**:
      On WorkspacePane mount (and whenever `sessionId` changes), fetch the session via the existing R2 session-restore endpoint OR add a GET sibling to the new PATCH (`GET /api/ai/chat/sessions/{sessionId}/tabs` returning `{ tabs, activeTabId }`). Call `manager.restoreFromPersistence(...)`. Wrap in try/catch — on failure, log via `errorTelemetry` (task 013) and continue with empty state (degrade gracefully).

      Failure mode: if restore takes &gt;500ms, NFR-02 (session restore p95 &lt;500ms) is at risk. Measure during testing.
    </step>
    <step order="9" name="Tests — BFF unit tests for SessionPersistenceService.SaveTabsAsync">
      In the existing BFF test project (or new file under `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/Sessions/`), add tests:
      - SaveTabs_NoExistingSession_ReturnsFalse
      - SaveTabs_WithEmptyList_SetsEmptyTabsField
      - SaveTabs_WithMultipleTabs_PersistsAllAndOrder
      - SaveTabs_UpdatesActiveTabId
      - SaveTabs_OldSessionWithoutTabsField_BackwardsCompatible (round-trip: load a Cosmos doc that pre-dates the schema, save it back — the new field is added cleanly)
      Use NSubstitute or Moq matching existing project patterns. Mock Cosmos container or use the existing test fixture if there is one.
    </step>
    <step order="10" name="Tests — Frontend manager tests for serialize/restore">
      Add to the existing `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/workspace/__tests__/WorkspaceTabManager.test.ts`:
      - serializeForPersistence_emptyManager_returnsEmptyTabsArray
      - serializeForPersistence_homeOnly_excludesHomeTab
      - serializeForPersistence_threeWidgetTabs_returnsAllInOrder
      - restoreFromPersistence_emptyManager_addsAllTabs
      - restoreFromPersistence_managerWithExistingNonHomeTabs_noOps (safety: don't clobber active session)
      - restoreFromPersistence_setsActiveTabIdIfInSet
      - restoreFromPersistence_invalidWidgetType_gracefullySkips
    </step>
    <step order="11" name="Manual smoke test the acceptance criterion">
      In a deployed environment (or local Vite dev with mock BFF), perform the exact NFR-09 acceptance test:
      1. Open SpaarkeAi welcome state.
      2. From the Context pane GetStartedCards, open 3 wizards as Workspace tabs (e.g., Create Matter, Create Project, Find Similar).
      3. Verify 3 non-Home tabs + Home = 4 tabs total.
      4. Refresh the page (Ctrl+R / Cmd+R).
      5. Verify ALL 3 non-Home tabs restored, in the same order, with the same active selection.
      Document the result in `notes/nfr-09-verification.md`.
    </step>
    <step order="12" name="Final verification + status updates">
      Run quality gates:
      - `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/` — 0 errors, no new warnings
      - `dotnet test` on the BFF test project (ignore the pre-existing 49 broken tests flagged in task 051 — verify your new tests pass in isolation if needed)
      - `npm run build` in `src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components` (if shared lib touched) — should not be
      - `npm run build` in `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi` — clean
      - Manual smoke test (step 11) PASS
      Update task 065 POML → completed. Update TASK-INDEX row 065 → ✅. Update task 063 follow-up note → resolved.
    </step>
  </steps>

