  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">StoredSession.cs has a `Tabs: List&lt;StoredWorkspaceTab&gt;` field with `[JsonPropertyName("tabs")]` and a default empty list (backwards compatible with older Cosmos documents).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">SessionPersistenceService has a method that persists tabs + activeTabId for a given sessionId/tenantId; verified by unit test that loads + saves a session.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">A `PATCH /api/ai/chat/sessions/{sessionId}/tabs` endpoint exists with the same auth + rate-limit filter chain as the sibling `/messages` endpoint (verified by `git diff` showing `.AddAiAuthorizationFilter().RequireRateLimiting(...)` on the MapPatch / MapPost line).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">WorkspaceTabManager has `serializeForPersistence()` returning `{tabs, activeTabId}` excluding the Home tab and the React Component field.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">WorkspaceTabManager has `restoreFromPersistence(snapshot)` that re-hydrates non-Home tabs by re-resolving each widgetType through the registry; no-ops if manager already has non-Home tabs.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">WorkspacePane.tsx writes tabs through to BFF on mutation (debounced ~200ms) via `authenticatedFetch` from `@spaarke/auth`; no `accessToken` props.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">WorkspacePane.tsx restores tabs on mount; on failure emits telemetry via `errorTelemetry` and degrades gracefully (empty state).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Manual smoke: open 3 non-Home tabs → refresh page → all 3 tabs (and active selection) restored. Evidence in `notes/nfr-09-verification.md`.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/` succeeds with 0 errors and no new warnings vs baseline.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`npm run build` in `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi` succeeds with 0 errors.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Standalone LegalWorkspace continues to function identically (FR-25 not regressed) — the change is SpaarkeAi-only.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    This task was opened in response to task 063 surfacing the NFR-09 gap (UQ-03 confirmed). It was foreseen in spec.md (UQ-03), design.md §H, plan.md R-5, and README.md R-5 as a possible follow-on; the project owner chose strict NFR-09 compliance (open task now) over deferral (Phase H follow-up).

    Frontend/backend coordination: this is the only Wave-7-style task remaining before Phase G deploy. After task 065 lands, Phase G (070 deploy + 071-074 smoke) can proceed.

    Performance note: write-through must be debounced (~200ms) so that a FIFO eviction (which adds + removes in rapid succession) doesn't flood the BFF. Restore on mount must complete &lt;500ms to preserve NFR-02 (session restore p95 &lt;500ms). Measure during smoke test; if restore is slow, consider including tabs in the existing R2 session-restore response payload (avoids a second round trip).

    Cosmos schema evolution: the Tabs field is purely additive (defaults to empty list). Older session documents without the field deserialise cleanly. No migration script needed.
  </notes>

  <execution>
